SENATE BILL 588
M2 6lr2005
By: Senator Simonaire
Introduced and read first time: February 5, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 2, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Natural Resources – Complimentary Fishing and Hunting Licenses – Alterations
3 FOR the purpose of altering certain requirements and authorizations for the issuance of
4 certain complimentary fishing and hunting licenses; requiring the Department of
5 Natural Resources to compile certain statistics relating to complimentary hunting
6 licenses at a certain time each year; and generally relating to complimentary hunting
7 and fishing licenses.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
9 Article – Natural Resources
10 Section 4–607(a)(1) and (b), 4–745(e), 4–1004.1(a) and (e)(2), 10–301(l), 10–301.3,
11 and 10–303
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 BY adding to
15 Article – Natural Resources
16 Section 4–1004.1(e)(4)
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
20 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
21 Article – Natural Resources
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0588*

2 SENATE BILL 588
1 4–607.
2 (a) (1) The Department may issue annually a complimentary angler’s license
3 to the President of the United States, the governor of any state, and any official OR
4 ENFORCEMENT OFFICER of the game and fish department of any other state THAT
5 RECIPROCALLY OFFERS A COMPLIMENTARY ANGLER’S LICENSE.
6 (b) Not more than 20 complimentary angler’s licenses ISSUED UNDER
7 SUBSECTION (A)(1) OF THIS SECTION for each state other than Maryland shall be
8 outstanding at any time.
9 4–745.
10 (e) (1) In this subsection, “former prisoner of war” means a person who, while
11 an active service member, was forcibly detained or interned in the line of duty by an enemy
12 government or its agents, or a hostile force, during a period of armed conflict.
13 (2) The Department may issue a lifetime complimentary Chesapeake Bay
14 and coastal sport fishing license to any Maryland resident who certifies that the resident
15 is:
16 (i) A former prisoner of war;
17 (ii) An American veteran who the U.S. Department of Veterans
18 Affairs determines is unemployable; or
19 (iii) A 100% service connected disabled American veteran.
20 (3) The Department may issue a lifetime complimentary Chesapeake Bay
21 and coastal sport fishing license to an out–of–state person:
22 (i) Who certifies that the person is:
23 1. A former prisoner of war;
24 2. An American veteran who the U.S. Department of
25 Veterans Affairs determines is unemployable; or
26 3. A 100% service connected disabled American veteran; and
27 (ii) Whose state of residence extends similar privileges to former
28 prisoners of war, American veterans who the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs
29 determines are unemployable, or 100% service connected disabled American veterans of
30 this State.

