19 10–301.
20 (l) When the Department has adequate computer capability, the Department
21 shall compile statistics after the close of the hunting season each year concerning [the]:
22 (1) THE sale of hunting licenses for the previous season, including the
23 names, addresses, counties of residence, and ages of the persons who purchased the hunting
24 licenses and the types of hunting licenses sold;
25 (2) THE NUMBER OF ANNUAL COMPLIMENTARY HUNTING LICENSES
26 ISSUED FOR THE PREVIOUS SEASON, INCLUDING THE NAMES, OCCUPATIONS, AND
27 STATES OF RESIDENCE OF THE PERSONS WHO WERE ISSUED THE ANNUAL
28 COMPLIMENTARY HUNTING LICENSES;
29 (3) THE NUMBER OF LIFETIME COMPLIMENTARY HUNTING LICENSES
30 ISSUED FOR THE PREVIOUS SEASON AND IN TOTAL, INCLUDING THE NAMES,
31 ELIGIBILITY CATEGORIES, AND STATES OF RESIDENCE OF THE PERSONS WHO WERE
32 ISSUED THE LIFETIME COMPLIMENTARY HUNTING LICENSES; AND

SENATE BILL 588 5
1 (4) THE TOTAL NUMBER OF HUNTING LICENSES THAT ARE NO
2 LONGER ISSUED BY THE DEPARTMENT THAT REMAIN VALID.
3 10–301.3.
4 (a) There is a commemorative lifetime hunting license.
5 (b) The Department shall issue a limited number of commemorative lifetime
6 hunting licenses to certain nonprofit organizations, consistent with eligibility criteria
7 developed by the Department, until December 31, 2011.
8 (c) [Nonprofit organizations issued hunting licenses under this section may, in
9 cooperation with the Department, market and sell the hunting licenses] EXCEPT FOR THE
10 INITIAL SALE BY A NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION, A COMMEMORATIVE LIFETIME
11 HUNTING LICENSE IS NOT TRANSFERRABLE.
12 (d) [All proceeds from sales of hunting licenses under this section shall be used
13 by the Department to fund conservation law enforcement by the Natural Resources Police
14 Force.
15 (e)] The Department may adopt regulations to carry out the provisions of this
16 section.
17 10–303.
18 (a) (1) The Department [annually] may issue ANNUALLY a complimentary
19 hunting license to the President of the United States, the governor of any state, or [an]
20 ANY official or [an] enforcement officer of the game and fish management agency of
21 [another] ANY OTHER state which reciprocally offers complimentary hunting licenses.
22 (2) (i) Subject to the requirements of § 10–301.1 of this subtitle, the
23 Department may issue a lifetime complimentary hunting license to a Maryland resident
24 who certifies that the resident is:
25 1. A former prisoner of war;
26 2. An American veteran who the U.S. Department of
27 Veterans Affairs determines is unemployable; or
28 3. A 100% service connected disabled American veteran.
29 (ii) Subject to the requirements of § 10–301.1 of this subtitle, the
30 Department may issue a lifetime complimentary hunting license to an out–of–state person:
31 1. Who certifies that the person is:

6 SENATE BILL 588
1 A. A former prisoner of war;
2 B. An American veteran who the U.S. Department of
3 Veterans Affairs determines is unemployable; or
