9 (3) A complimentary HUNTING license is not transferable AND SHALL BE
10 ISSUED WITHOUT A FEE.
11 (b) For the purposes of this section, “former prisoner of war” means a person who,
12 while an active service member, was forcibly detained or interned in the line of duty by an
13 enemy government or its agents, or a hostile force, during a period of armed conflict.
14 (C) NOT MORE THAN 20 COMPLIMENTARY HUNTING LICENSES ISSUED
15 UNDER SUBSECTION (A)(1) OF THIS SECTION FOR EACH STATE OTHER THAN
16 MARYLAND SHALL BE OUTSTANDING AT ANY TIME.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
18 1, 2026.
